stylometry: You must have enough inventory on hand to supply the demand but as little as possible to minimize holding costs.  Things you have to consider when determining how much to order is demand, lead time, and holding costs.  You have to minimize these costs in order to maximize the profit, but at the same time have enough inventory to supply the demand.  There is a common question to ask yourself, this is order little often or order lots more infrequently. This mostly falls back on what are the holding costs and the demand at the time.
